description: Congress criticized PM Modi for previously dismissing Rahul Gandhi's caste census demand as "urban naxal mindset," while now BJP leaders are claiming credit for the government's decision to enumerate caste in the delayed census. The CWC will convene to discuss the government's decision and potentially increase pressure on related demands, highlighting BJP's shift under Rahul's influence.
title: Congress dismisses caste census announcement as ‘diversionary tactic’ of government

description: BJP lauded the Centre's decision to include caste enumeration in the upcoming census, emphasizing the NDA's dedication to social justice. Union Minister Dharmendra Pradhan criticized Congress for its alleged hypocrisy on OBC welfare, citing historical opposition to reservations by the Nehru-Gandhi family. He contrasted this with PM Modi's commitment to social justice through effective policies.
title: Government call on caste count game changer, exposes Congress: BJP

description: Indians are accessing credit much earlier, with the average age for first-time borrowers dropping significantly across generations. This shift is driven by increased disposable income, pre-approved loans from banks, and the availability of unsecured credit products like credit cards and personal loans. The Jan Dhan-Aadhaar-Mobile trinity has also streamlined borrower tracking, contributing to this trend.
title: Lend, baby, lend: Borrowers getting younger

description: Apple CEO Tim Cook announced that most US iPhones would be sourced from India due to rising US-China tariff tensions. The tariffs on Chinese imports could cost Apple up to $900 million. Despite these pressures, Apple reported strong earnings for the first three months of the year, with a profit increase of 4.8% and a revenue rise of 5.1%.
title: 'Most US iPhones to be sourced in India': Apple CEO amid trade war with China

description: Amid heightened tensions, the Indian Navy has intensified its presence in the Arabian Sea, issuing warnings to ships near its firing drill zone, close to where the Pakistan Navy is also conducting exercises.
title: Navy intensifies muscle-flexing against Pak as small arms fire continues across LoC
Now, outsiders can’t buy farm land in 11 of 13 Uttarakhand districts
'Occupy North East if India attacks Pakistan': Yunus government aide
Pahalgama attack aftermath: Pak shuts Wagah gate, leaves its citizens stranded
Those who convert lose SC status: HC

description: The Trump administration has approved a $131 million sale of maritime domain awareness software and equipment to India. This sale aims to bolster India's maritime capabilities and strategic posture in the Indo-Pacific region. The US believes this will strengthen the US-Indian strategic relationship and promote stability and security in the region.
title: US clears $131 million sale of defence software, equipment to India

description: In a landmark decision, the Supreme Court overturned a trial court's acquittal of a man for sexually assaulting a 10-year-old girl 32 years ago. The apex court upheld a Gujarat High Court ruling, sentencing the now 54-year-old convict to 10 years in prison. The SC criticized the initial acquittal, highlighting the overwhelming evidence against the accused.
title: Acquitted by Guj judge in 1994, man sent to jail by SC for raping 10-yr-old
Ailing bride in arms, man takes 'saat phere' in hospital
'Don't think you've won the war': Amit Shah to Pahalgam perpetrators

description: The Delhi high court has found Yoga guru Ramdev in contempt for defying an earlier undertaking regarding disparaging remarks against Hamdard's Rooh Afza. The court expressed concern over Ramdev's lack of control and ordered him to remove an offensive social media video within 24 hours.
title: HC warns Ramdev of contempt, says take down video targeting Rooh Afza
Impotency slur can't be abetment to suicide a month later, says SC
India's billion plus stories will fuel economic growth: PM Modi

description: The National Human Rights Commission has urged authorities nationwide to protect vulnerable populations from rising heatwave dangers. Citing NCRB data showing 3,798 heat-related deaths between 2018 and 2022, the NHRC has directed 11 states, including Uttar Pradesh and Maharashtra, to implement preemptive measures. These include providing shelters, adjusting work hours, and ensuring treatment for heat illnesses.
title: Take measures to protect vulnerable people from heat: NHRC to 11 states
We are duty-bound to order performance audit of laws: SC

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai cautioned that the US Department of Justice's antitrust remedies could jeopardize Google Search, potentially leading the company to discontinue its flagship product. Pichai argued that the DOJ's proposal to share Google's search index with competitors at minimal cost would stifle innovation.
title: Sundar Pichai warns US' 'extraordinary' plans for Chrome may ‘kill’ Google

description: President Trump announced Marco Rubio as the interim National Security Advisor, succeeding Mike Waltz, while also nominating Waltz as the United Nations Ambassador. Waltz's departure follows criticism and reports of staff dismissals within the National Security Council. Trump expressed confidence in both Rubio and Waltz to prioritize national interests and enhance global safety in their respective roles.
title: Trump makes Rubio interim NSA, nominates Mike Waltz for UN ambassador

description: Donald Trump threatened sanctions on Iranian oil buyers, halting US business ties, after nuclear talks were delayed. Oman cited logistical reasons for postponing the meeting, while Iran affirmed commitment to a fair agreement. Tensions rise amid stalled negotiations, with the US hinting at military action and Iran considering nuclear weapons development.
title: Trump threatens to impose sanctions against nations buying oil from Iran

description: In Bhubaneswar, a Nepalese student was found dead in her hostel room at a private university, marking the second such incident in two and a half months. Police have confirmed the death as a suicide and are investigating the circumstances.
title: Another Nepali girl found dead in hostel room of Bhubaneswar university

description: Mumbai Indians defeated Rajasthan Royals by 100 runs in a spectacular IPL 2025 match. Ryan Rickelton's powerful 61 and Karn Sharma's effective bowling were key to Mumbai's sixth consecutive win. Rickelton's aggressive batting set a strong foundation. Sharma's disciplined bowling dismantled Rajasthan's batting lineup. Mumbai Indians strengthened their playoff chances with this victory.
title: IPL: Rickelton, Karn shine as MI throw RR out of playoffs race

description: Yuzvendra Chahal's exclusion from the BCCI's annual contracts sparks questions about his future with Team India. Astrologer Greenstone Lobo attributes this dip to Pluto's shift into the "Grey Lizard Avatar," signifying transformation. Despite competition from younger talents like Axar Patel and Kuldeep Yadav, Chahal's dedication suggests continued success in the IPL and other tournaments.
title: Is this the end of Yuzvendra Chahal's Team India career?

description: Teenage sensation Vaibhav Suryavanshi experienced a dramatic turn of events in the IPL 2025. After a record-breaking century, he was dismissed for a duck against Mumbai Indians, triggering a wave of social media reactions. Mumbai Indians set a formidable target of 217/2, putting Rajasthan Royals under pressure, further intensifying after Vaibhav's early dismissal, and RR's chase looked shaky.
title: Memes break internet as 14-yo Vaibhav Suryavanshi flops in RR vs MI

description: Mike Waltz is expected to be removed from his position as US National Security Advisor after a security breach involving the Signal app. Waltz mistakenly included a journalist in a group chat discussing sensitive military operations against Houthi rebels. This incident eroded President Trump's confidence in Waltz, leading to his impending dismissal.
title: Signal app 'security scandal' may have claimed 1st victim as Trump plans...

description: Amidst rising tensions between India and Pakistan following the Pahalgam terror attack, the UK government is calling for de-escalation and dialogue. A Tory peer has urged Britain to directly intervene by appointing a special emissary to facilitate discussions. Concerns have also been raised regarding protests in London, including a Pakistani diplomat's threatening gesture towards Indian demonstrators.
title: UK urges India, Pak to de-escalate situation, says it's ‘incredibly dangerous’

description: A controversy has erupted within the Bengal BJP as senior leader Dilip Ghosh's attendance at the Jagannath Dham temple inauguration with Mamata Banerjee sparks outrage. Swapan Dasgupta has criticized Ghosh's actions as a "betrayal," intensifying the internal conflict. This division surfaces amidst the BJP's efforts to challenge Banerjee over the Murshidabad violence, highlighting a significant rift within the party.
title: 'Apparent betrayal': Turmoil in BJP as Dilip Ghosh visits Mamata’s event

description: After a record-breaking century in the previous game, Vaibhav Suryavanshi, Rajasthan Royals' young star, had a disappointing outing, dismissed for a duck against Mumbai Indians. Mumbai Indians capitalized on favorable batting conditions, with Rohit Sharma and Ryan Rickelton setting up a strong foundation. Suryakumar Yadav and Hardik Pandya's explosive innings propelled MI to a formidable total of 217.
title: Dravid can't hide disappointment as Suryavanshi falls for a duck

description: A recent Oxfam report reveals a stark disparity in income growth, with global CEO pay soaring by 50% since 2019 to $4.3 million annually, while average worker wages have barely budged, increasing only 0.9% over the same period. This widening gap exacerbates financial struggles for workers, particularly in regions like India, where living wages fall short of decent living expenses.
title: Millions for bosses, peanuts for workers: Salary of CEOs spike by 50% since 2019

description: President Trump is reportedly dismissing National Security Advisor Michael Waltz after a security breach involving a journalist in a Signal chat. This comes amidst a pattern of high turnover in key positions during Trump's administrations, making it difficult for international counterparts like India's NSA Ajit Doval to build stable relationships.
title: NSA Waltz facing axe as churn continues in Trump's second term

description: During the Mumbai Indians vs Rajasthan Royals IPL 2025 match, Rohit Sharma's LBW decision was overturned by DRS, sparking laughter and a viral reaction. The incident provided comic relief in the high-stakes game. Riyan Parag chose to bowl first, while Hardik Pandya expressed confidence despite also preferring to bowl, setting the stage for an intense contest.
title: Rohit Sharma's reaction goes viral after DRS overturns 'out' call

description: India's fastest T20 centurion, Urvil Patel, along with Aman Khan and Salman Nizar, participated in mid-season trials for Chennai Super Kings. Patel impressed with scores of 41 off 20 and 50 off 20, drawing praise from CSK members. Despite his impressive Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy performance, he remains unpicked.
title: CSK call India's fastest T20 centurion for mid-season IPL 2025 trials

description: Rohit Sharma achieved a significant milestone, becoming the second player to surpass 6000 runs for a single T20 franchise, Mumbai Indians, during the IPL 2025 match against Rajasthan Royals. He trails only Virat Kohli in this record. Rohit leads a list that includes legends like James Vince (Hampshire), Suresh Raina (CSK), and MS Dhoni (CSK).
title: Rohit Sharma's record leaves Dhoni and Raina behind by a mile

description: Despite geopolitical tensions, the BSE Sensex saw a nearly 4% increase in April, fueled by foreign investment, monsoon forecasts, and trade agreement prospects. Attractive valuations and RBI rate cuts further boosted market sentiment. While Q4 earnings and global cues will influence future performance, analysts remain optimistic about the long-term outlook.
title: Sensex rises nearly 4% in April on FII inflows, monsoon hopes & trade optimism
Signalgate fallout? Trump's NSA Mike Waltz, deputy likely to step down

description: Following a recent terror attack in Pahalgam, Kashmir, which resulted in the tragic loss of 26 Indian tourists, Pakistan's Olympic javelin champion Arshad Nadeem's Instagram account has been blocked in India. This action comes as the Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi vows to bring the perpetrators to justice and strengthen the nation's resolve against terrorism.
title: Arshad Nadeem's account blocked in India — but not Shahid Afridi's

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack that claimed 26 lives, Union Home Minister Amit Shah issued a strong warning, vowing that the perpetrators would face severe consequences. He asserted the Modi government's commitment to eradicating terrorism from India, emphasizing that those responsible will be held accountable.
title: 'Chun chun ke jawab milega': Shah vows to avenge Pahalgam attack

description: Rajani Shaw, wife of detained BSF jawan Purnam Kumar Shaw, sought answers in Pathankot regarding her husband's situation in Pakistan. BSF officers in Firozpur assured her that Purnam was safe and his release was likely soon, with talks underway with Pakistan Rangers.
title: 'He's safe': Pregnant wife of BSF jawan in Pakistan custody

description: Rajasthan Royals will face Mumbai Indians without Sanju Samson, who is still recovering from a side strain. Riyan Parag leads the team in his absence, having won the toss and elected to bowl first. The team is also dealing with injuries to key players like Wanindu Hasaranga and Sandeep Sharma, with Kumar Kartikeya and Akash Madhwal stepping in.
title: IPL 2025: Why Samson is not playing for RR against MI

description: Rajasthan Royals pacer Sandeep Sharma has been ruled out for the remainder of the IPL 2025 season after sustaining a finger fracture.Despite the injury, he displayed remarkable determination by continuing to bowl in the last match."The franchise extend their best wishes for his full and swift recovery. The team management is currently in the process of finalizing a suitable replacement, with an official announcement expected soon," Rajasthan Royals said in a statement.
title: Massive blow! Rajasthan Royals' star ruled out of IPL 2025
News brief: Rajnath speaks to US defence secy; Delhi HC pulls up Ramdev; and more

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, China offers Pakistan diplomatic support but signals limited intervention, prioritizing its own strategic interests. Despite the proclaimed all-weather friendship, Beijing's focus remains on internal stability, managing trade tensions, and de-escalating with India. Pakistan's reliance on China for unconditional support may be a miscalculation, as Beijing balances regional dynamics and its own priorities.
title: Pahalgam fallout: Why Xi may not come to rescue of 'China's Israel'

description: Shikhar Dhawan, following a publicised divorce, is rumoured to be in a relationship with Sophie Shine, an Irish professional based in Abu Dhabi. Speculation ignited after Shine posted a photo of them together, further fueled by public appearances and Dhawan's subtle confirmation of dating someone. Shine, a Product Consultant, reportedly met Dhawan in Dubai, and their bond has grown steadily.
title: Shikhar Dhawan's Irish girlfriend makes viral post about their relationship

description: Amid national grief over the Pahalgam terror attack that killed 26, including Navy Lieutenant Vinay Narwal, his wife Himanshi Narwal, a PhD scholar, passionately appealed for peace, urging people not to turn against Muslims or Kashmiris. Lieutenant Narwal was honored with full military honors, and his funeral took place in Karnal, where thousands gathered to pay their respects.
title: 'We want justice but ...': Wife of Navy officer killed in J&K attack

description: Phoebe Gates, daughter of Bill Gates, revealed on a podcast the challenges and humorous moments of introducing her romantic interests to her father. She shared anecdotes about his socially awkward demeanor, attributing it to Asperger's syndrome. Phoebe also mentioned an incident from high school and how she now uses her father's quirks as a test for potential partners.
title: 'Terrifying for the guy ...' Bill Gates daughter on bringing men home to her dad

description: Amid escalating tensions following the Pahalgam terrorist attack, Defence Minister Rajnath Singh engaged in discussions with his US counterpart, Pete Hegseth. This dialogue occurred alongside increased ceasefire violations by Pakistan along the LoC, prompting India to respond firmly and caution Pakistan regarding these breaches.
title: 'US backs India's right to defend itself': Defence minister Rajnath after call with Hegseth

description: AAP MP Sanjay Singh criticised the government's timing of the caste census announcement, alleging it was a distraction from the Pahalgam terror attack where 26 tourists were killed. He questioned PM Modi's decision to campaign in Bihar instead of addressing the security failure. Interestingly, when former Prime Minister VP Singh had announced the implementation of the Mandal Commission report in 1990, his timing was also questioned by the then opposition led by Congress citing the situation in Kashmir.
title: When Rajiv Gandhi questioned Mandal report move amid Kashmir tension

description: In April 2025, the Indian auto market saw mixed results. Maruti Suzuki's total sales increased by 7%, while Hyundai and Tata Motors experienced declines. Mahindra & Mahindra and Kia India reported strong growth, particularly in the SUV segment. Toyota Kirloskar Motor and JSW MG Motor India also saw significant sales increases, with the MG Windsor EV leading in its segment.
title: April 2025 Car Sales: Maruti, Mahindra, Toyota grow, Tata Motors faces decline

description: Following a thorough investigation into safety issues stemming from a January crash, HAL's ALH Dhruv variants for the Indian Army and Air Force have been cleared for operations. This decision follows recommendations from a Defect Investigation Committee and a phased resumption plan. HAL has defended its platforms against criticism, emphasizing its collaboration with the armed forces.
title: Dhruv choppers get all clear for ops after safety review
'Is Buddha needed for Buddhism?' Elon Musk on stepping down from DOGE

description: Pakistan's aviation authorities have announced a temporary closure of specific airspace sections over Karachi and Lahore from May 1 to May 31, 2025, citing security concerns. This precautionary measure, implemented daily between 4:00 AM and 8:00 AM, necessitates flight adjustments, including cancellations by Pakistan International Airlines. The closure occurs amidst heightened regional tensions following the Pahalgam terror attack in India.
title: Pakistan partially closes Karachi, Lahore airspace till May 31

description: India’s star batter Virat Kohli shared a heartfelt message on Instagram to celebrate the birthday of his wife, actress Anushka Sharma. "To my best friend, my life partner, my safe space, my best half, my everything. You’re the guiding light of all of our lives. We love you so much more everyday. Happy birthday my love @anushkasharma," Virat wrote.
title: Virat Kohli calls Anushka Sharma his 'safe space'

description: Amid heightened tensions following the Pahalgam terror attack, the Indian Navy has significantly increased its presence in the Arabian Sea. Naval warships are on high alert, conducting anti-ship and anti-aircraft firing exercises within India's EEZ to demonstrate combat readiness. The Indian Coast Guard is also coordinating with the Navy to enhance surveillance near the Gujarat coast.
title: Warships on high alert, Navy intensifies ops in Arabian Sea

description: Chennai Super Kings' disappointing IPL 2025 season has ended with early elimination, raising questions about their strategy, especially regarding Ravichandran Ashwin. The expensive signing has been underutilized, drawing criticism from Harbhajan Singh. He suggests Ashwin's exclusion, despite favorable conditions, cost CSK a crucial match against Punjab Kings, while other underperforming players continue to feature in the team.
title: 'You didn't pay Rs 10 cr for Ashwin to ... ': Harbhajan tears into CSK

description: India's Goods and Services Tax (GST) revenue soared to a record Rs 2.37 lakh crore in April, marking a 12.6% year-on-year increase. This figure surpasses the previous high of Rs 2.10 lakh crore from April 2024.
title: GST collections in April hit record high of Rs 2.37 lakh crore

description: Asaduddin Owaisi urged the BJP government to move beyond rhetoric and take decisive action against Pakistan by focusing on Pakistan-occupied Kashmir (PoK). He reminded the government of the Parliament's resolution asserting India's claim over PoK. Owaisi highlighted past terror attacks and emphasized the need to eradicate terrorism, noting a national consensus among opposition parties on the issue.
title: 'Iss baar ghar mein ghus kar baith jana': Owaisi urges govt to take PoK

description: Kris Srikkanth has criticized Lucknow Super Giants' handling of Rishabh Pant, questioning Justin Langer and Zaheer Khan's decisions. Pant, acquired for a substantial sum, has underperformed, and Srikkanth questioned his late appearance in a recent match. Anil Kumble also expressed concerns about Pant's batting position and perceived frustration, highlighting potential mismanagement.
title: Kris Srikkanth slams LSG coach for handling Rishabh Pant poorly

description: Microsoft navigated initial US tariffs with minimal direct product exposure, emphasizing software solutions to mitigate client pressures. CEO Satya Nadella highlighted software's role in combating inflationary pressures, focusing on customer support and shared gains. While shielded by its software focus, Microsoft faces potential indirect effects from reduced client spending and increased equipment costs, particularly for AI-related hardware.
title: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella has a ‘solution’ to reduce impact of Trump Tariffs

description: Suryakumar Yadav reflected on his Mumbai Indians debut, revealing pre-game jitters and early struggles before becoming a key player. He recounted his pivotal 2018 season, opening unexpectedly and scoring over 500 runs, and shared insights from the tense 2019 IPL final. He made his IPL debut for Mumbai Indians in the 2012 season, playing against Pune Warriors at the Wankhede Stadium. However, his first outing was short-lived as he was dismissed for a duck—the only game he featured in that season.
title: 'When I didn't see my name in the squad ... ': Suryakumar Yadav

description: Aston Martin has unveiled the DBX S, a high-performance SUV slated for release in late 2025. Boasting a 717 bhp engine and a top speed of 193 mph, it's the most powerful ICE SUV ever. Enhanced with design tweaks, carbon-fibre elements, and superior agility, the DBX S aims to surpass rivals like Lamborghini Urus SE and Ferrari Purosangue.
title: Aston Martin unveils new DBX S with increased horsepower engine, new features

description: Bank Holidays May 2025: In May 2025, bank holidays will vary across Indian states, impacting banking services. Closures are scheduled for Labour Day/Maharashtra Day, Rabindranath Tagore Jayanti, Buddha Purnima, State Day, Kazi Nazrul Islam's Birthday, and Maharana Pratap Jayanti.
title: Bank Holidays in May 2025: Check state-wise full list

description: The Election Commission of India is enhancing the electoral process through three major initiatives. These include electronic acquisition of death registration data for prompt deletion of deceased voters, a redesigned Voter Information Slip for improved user experience, and standard photo identity cards for Booth Level Officers to boost voter outreach and confidence.
title: EC takes 3 big steps to improve accuracy of electoral rolls

description: In a joint operation, the Border Security Force and Punjab Police seized a significant cache of arms and ammunition from Bharopal village in Amritsar district. The recovered items included two hand grenades, three pistols with six magazines, and 50 live rounds. A BSF official highlighted that this coordinated effort averted a potential major terror incident.
title: 'Prevented major terror incident': BSF-Punjab Police bust arms haul in Amritsar

description: Cybersecurity researchers are alerting Indian internet users about a surge in hacking attempts originating from Pakistan, potentially linked to geopolitical tensions. Hackers are distributing malicious PDF files disguised as official documents to compromise devices. Experts warn of escalating cyber warfare, urging caution with unsolicited messages and emphasizing the need for updated security measures.
title: Researchers warn Pakistani hackers targeting PCs, laptops & mobile: What to know

description: Pakistani actress Hania Aamir, known for her Bollywood fandom, especially for Shah Rukh Khan, once expressed her desire to meet the superstar. However, escalating political tensions between India and Pakistan have impacted online accessibility. Following a terror attack in Jammu and Kashmir, the Indian government banned several Pakistani media outlets.
title: When Pak actress Hania Aamir expressed her desire to meet Shah Rukh Khan

description: Elon Musk has strongly refuted a Wall Street Journal report alleging that Tesla's board initiated a CEO search. Musk labeled the report as deliberately false and unethical, emphasizing the absence of an unequivocal denial from the Tesla board prior to publication.
title: Breach of Ethics, says Elon Musk as report claims Tesla Board wanted to fire him

description: The Delhi High Court has found Yoga guru Ramdev in prima facie contempt for violating a previous order regarding his "sharbat jihad" remarks against Hamdard's Rooh Afza. Justice Amit Bansal noted that Ramdev published a video with objectionable content despite the court's directive prohibiting such statements. The court expressed strong disapproval of Ramdev's remarks, deeming them "indefensible.""He (Ramdev) is not in control of anyone. He lives in his own world," the judge remarked.
title: 'He lives in his own world': Delhi HC pulls up Ramdev over 'Sharbat jihad' row

description: There has never been a doubt about Prabhsimran Singh’s talent. There was a reason why in 2018, Kings XI Punjab (now Punjab Kings), Mumbai Indians, and Royal Challengers Bangalore were involved in a fierce bidding war for the then 18-year-old. Prabhsimran ended up being a teen crorepati when he was picked for Rs 4.8 crores by the Punjab franchise. In 2020, he impressed Sachin Tendulkar with his bat swing, but it took him five years to find that consistency.
title: How a 'gedi' chat gave PBKS' Prabhsimran Singh a reality check

description: The Supreme Court dismissed petitions requesting a judicial investigation, overseen by a retired SC judge, into the deadly terror attack in Jammu and Kashmir's Pahalgam that resulted in 26 fatalities. The court admonished the petitioners for filing Public Interest Litigations, stating that judges lack expertise in terror case investigations and cautioned against demoralizing the forces with such petitions.
title: Want to demoralise forces? SC raps PIL seeking judicial probe into Pahalgam attack

description: Congress workers in Hyderabad celebrated the Centre's decision to conduct a caste census by pouring milk on posters of Rahul Gandhi and Telangana CM Revanth Reddy.
title: Watch: Cong workers pour milk on Rahul Gandhi’s poster to celebrate caste census push

description: Chennai Super Kings, led by MS Dhoni, faced elimination from the IPL playoff race after a four-wicket defeat against Punjab Kings at their home ground. Despite fifties from Shreyas Iyer and Prabhsimran Singh, and a hat-trick by Yuzvendra Chahal, PBKS secured the victory.
title: Final goodbye? MS Dhoni's heart-warming meet-and-greet with CSK owners goes viral

description: Lord's will host the 2026 Women's T20 World Cup final, marking a defining moment for women's cricket. The tournament, featuring 12 teams and 33 games, begins June 12, with the final set for July 5. Other venues include The Oval, Old Trafford, and Edgbaston, as England aims to build on the legacy of the 2017 World Cup.
title: Lord's to host 2026 Women's T20 World Cup final

description: The Income Tax Department has introduced new ITR-1 and ITR-4 forms for FY 2024-25, simplifying tax filing for individuals with long-term capital gains up to Rs 1.25 lakh from listed equities. These forms feature modifications for deductions and require detailed TDS information. This change aims to enhance taxpayer services and encourage voluntary compliance by reducing the complexity for small taxpayers.
title: Tax return: New ITR-1 form notified with major changes - check details

description: A Delhi court has granted the National Investigation Agency (NIA) permission to collect voice and handwriting samples from Tahawwur Hussain Rana, an accused in the 26/11 Mumbai terror attack. Rana, an associate of David Coleman Headley, was extradited to India after his appeal was dismissed by the US Supreme Court.
title: 26/11 attack: Court allows NIA to record Tahawwur Rana's voice, handwriting samples

description: Watier cosmetics' anti-aging cream has been recalled in Canada due to microbial contamination. Health Canada identified Lactobacillus pentosus, a probiotic, in the Age Control Supreme Sublime Advanced Rich day cream, sold at Shoppers Drug Mart and Amazon. While L. pentosus poses minimal health risks, the product failed to meet microbial standards.
title: Canada recalls popular anti-aging cream for failing safety tests

description: The BJP has criticized the Congress party regarding the inclusion of caste-based enumeration in the upcoming census, questioning their historical inaction. Union Minister Dharmendra Pradhan accused former PM Nehru of opposing caste-based reservations, leading to the discontinuation of caste census after 1931.
title: Caste census: BJP counters Cong's ‘sarkar tumhari, system humara’ slogan
Elon Musk denies Tesla CEO replacement plans amid board drama

description: Following the Union Cabinet's approval of caste-based data collection in the upcoming census, posters emerged outside Congress and RJD offices, celebrating leaders Rahul Gandhi and Lalu Prasad Yadav's advocacy for a caste census. Gandhi welcomed the decision but urged for a clear timeline, emphasizing it as an initial step towards comprehensive social reform, attributing the development to sustained political and public pressure.
title: 'Jhukti hai duniya': Rahul Gandhi posters crop up after Centre's caste census nod

description: Tesla's board has reportedly explored potential successors for Elon Musk, prompted by his involvement with the Trump administration. Shareholders are concerned about declining sales and Musk's political affiliations, which have led to protests and damage to Tesla facilities.
title: Is Tesla looking for a new CEO as Musk focuses on White House?

description: Pakistan has appointed its current ISI chief, Lt Gen Muhammad Asim Malik, as the new National Security Adviser amidst escalating tensions with India following the Pahalgam terror attack. This marks the first instance of a serving ISI director general holding both crucial positions simultaneously. The notification stated, "Lt Gen Muhammad Asim Malik HI (M), DG (I), shall hold the additional charge of the National Security Adviser, with immediate effect."
title: ISI chief gets additional role as NSA as India-Pakistan tensions flare

description: A protest occurred in Nainital's Mallital area. This followed the alleged rape of a minor girl by a contractor named Usman. The victim is a Class 7 student. Outraged community members gathered, demanding action. Protests spread, resulting in vandalism of shops. Police detained Usman. Investigations are underway to ensure justice for the victim and her family.
title: Shops vandalised, slogans raised in Nainital over rape of Class 7 girl

description: Labour Day, celebrated annually on May 1st, honors the contributions and struggles of workers worldwide. Originating from the 1886 Haymarket event, it acknowledges the labor movement's fight for fair conditions and decent pay. The day is marked by parades and speeches, emphasizing the dignity of work and worker rights, with quotes from notable figures highlighting labor's value.
title: International Labour Day 2025: 60+ Wishes & quotes to celebrate workers' rights

description: Chennai Super Kings' struggles continued as they suffered their eighth defeat in the ongoing IPL season, succumbing to Punjab Kings by 4 wickets. This loss marks their third consecutive defeat, leaving them at the bottom of the standings with only 4 points.
title: IPL 2025: Can MS Dhoni-led CSK still qualify for playoffs?

description: Apple dramatically increased iPhone exports from India to the US in March 2025, reaching 97.6% of total exports, driven by concerns over potential tariffs on Chinese goods. This shift involves expanding Indian production with manufacturers like Tata Electronics and Foxconn, aiming for a complete transition of US-bound iPhone production from China to India by 2026.
title: Move away from China? Apple exports 97.6% of iPhones to US from India

description: MS Dhoni criticized the Chennai Super Kings' batting performance after their four-wicket defeat to Punjab Kings, which resulted in their elimination from playoff contention. Despite Sam Curran's impressive 88 and support from Dewald Brevis, CSK fell short of a par score, according to Dhoni.
title: MS Dhoni blames batters after CSK bow out from playoff race in IPL 2025
No, Michelle Obama didn’t call herself a black man
Prince William to remove Harry and Meghan’s ‘HRH’ status: Report

description: Preity Zinta, co-owner of Punjab Kings, expressed her joy after their thrilling four-wicket victory over Chennai Super Kings. Punjab's successful chase of 191 was fueled by strong performances from openers and a captain's knock, securing a crucial win. Despite MS Dhoni's assessment that their score was slightly short, CSK's loss eliminated them from playoff contention.
title: Ting! Preity Zinta a 'happy girl' after PBKS' win over CSK

description: Sundar Pichai voiced strong objections to the DOJ's proposed remedies in Google's antitrust case, cautioning they could cripple Google Search and jeopardize user privacy. He argued that demands to share search data and potentially sell Chrome would undermine innovation and devalue Google's investments. Pichai also highlighted privacy risks associated with the data-sharing proposal.
title: Upset Google CEO calls US govt proposal to break Google: "So far-reaching, so …"

description: Karoline Leavitt, the US press secretary, shared a rare video tour of the White House, offering a glimpse into her daily life and responsibilities. She highlighted key areas like the press briefing room and her office, emphasizing the importance of communicating the President's message effectively. Leavitt underscored that the White House ultimately belongs to the American people.
title: Watch: Ever wonder what it's like to be at White House? US press secy shows you

description: The Indian government's decision to include caste enumeration in the upcoming census has ignited political debate, with the BJP and opposition Congress both vying for credit. While Congress claims it as a victory for Rahul Gandhi's advocacy, the BJP highlights Congress's historical opposition to caste-based census. The move aims to gather data on caste distribution for informed policy-making.
title: Who deserves credit? BJP, Congress lock horns over caste census decision

description: Dewald Brevis's stunning catch was a highlight for Chennai Super Kings (CSK) in a disappointing season, marked by their elimination from IPL 2025 playoffs after a loss to Punjab Kings. Sam Curran's brilliant 88 helped CSK reach 190, but Yuzvendra Chahal's hat-trick triggered a collapse.
title: CSK's Dewald Brevis plucks a stunner in three attempts

description: A departmental investigation has begun against A K Mulla. He is a driver with the North West Karnataka Road Transport Corporation. Mulla was seen offering Namaz inside a parked bus. Passengers were inside the bus at the time. A passenger recorded a video of the incident. The video went viral. Officials are investigating the circumstances surrounding the event.
title: Karnataka roadways bus driver offers namaz during duty hours, faces probe
'Stop playing deaf & dumb,' China claims Covid might’ve emerged in US first

description: US President Trump defended his tariff strategy despite economic slowdown signs, suggesting Americans might face fewer and costlier products. He insisted China would bear the brunt of the economic pain, dismissing recession concerns and attributing market jitters to his predecessor. While touting foreign investment, his administration faced criticism over contradictory messaging and the potential for economic instability due to trade tensions.
title: Trump plays down China tariff impact, says US kids may get '2 dolls instead of 30'

description: Pakistani forces have engaged in unprovoked firing across the Line of Control for the seventh consecutive day, prompting a proportionate response from the Indian Army in Kupwara, Uri, and Akhnoor. This ceasefire violation occurred despite recent talks between the Directors General of Military Operations of both nations, where India warned Pakistan against such actions.
title: Unprovoked firing by Pakistan continues for seventh straight day; India retaliates

description: A recent study highlights a potential risk: healthcare workers laundering uniforms at home may inadvertently spread antibiotic-resistant infections. Home washing machines often fail to adequately disinfect clothing, allowing dangerous bacteria to persist. Researchers suggest revising laundering guidelines and exploring on-site industrial machines in healthcare facilities to enhance patient safety and curb the spread of these pathogens.
title: Hospital germs survive common household washing machines, raising concerns

description: Tesla's board is reportedly seeking Elon Musk's successor amidst sinking stock prices and investor concerns over his focus on governmental duties. A major search firm has been engaged, though it's unclear if Musk is aware. With Musk dedicating significant time to the US government's Department of Government Efficiency, the board also aims to add an independent director.
title: Tesla opens search for a CEO to replace Elon Musk: Report
Who is Palwasha Mohammad? Pak Senator’s Ayodhya remarks spark outrage

description: Bhagwant Mann accuses BJP of bullying Punjab over water. He claims Haryana seeks excess water for irrigation. Mann asserts Punjab cannot spare water due to its own shortages. He alleges a BJP conspiracy to deprive Punjab of its water resources. Mann states Punjab will supply water to Haryana for drinking purposes only.
title: Punjab CM accuses Haryana, Centre of ‘bullying’ and ‘hooliganism’ over water

description: The recently surfaced autopsy and investigative report, which has not been independently verified, paints a gruesome picture of what allegedly happened during her captivity. According to the findings, Roshchyna had her brain removed, multiple bones broken, head shaved, and signs of electrocution on her body. She was reportedly subjected to drug injections and left without food for extended periods, resulting in severe physical deterioration.
title: 'Brain missing, bones broken': Chilling details emerge of Ukrainian journalist's death

description: After the success of 'Gadar 2,' Sunny Deol's 'Jaat,' co-starring Randeep Hooda, has completed 21 days in theaters. While it opened strongly with positive reviews, the film's momentum has slowed. 'Jaat' has earned ₹86.85 crore domestically and is now facing competition from Ajay Devgn’s ‘Raid 2,’ along with ‘Kesari 2’ and ‘Ground Zero.’
title: 'Jaat' box office day 21: Film slowly inches towards Rs 90 crore

description: Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang is advocating for the US government to ease export controls on AI technology, arguing that current restrictions hinder American companies' global competitiveness. He emphasizes that China is rapidly catching up in AI development, with companies like Huawei creating their own AI chips.
title: China is ..., says Nvidia CEO on the Big Question: Is China ahead of America in AI

description: US President Donald Trump is considering IBM and Raytheon Technologies, among others, to modernize the nation's aging air traffic control system. This push follows a tragic mid-air collision near Washington's Reagan Airport. A $12.5 billion proposal is under consideration to replace control towers and radar systems.
title: Trump lists IBM, Raytheon among 5 firms to modernise US air traffic system

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, ISI and the Pakistan government have heightened security for Lashkar-e-Taiba chief Hafiz Saeed, fearing a covert operation. Former Special Service Group commandos have been assigned to his protection, with increased security at his residences. Lawrence Bishnoi syndicate has also threatened retaliation for the Pahalgam killings, vowing to target a high-value individual in Pakistan.
title: Pak steps up LeT chief Hafiz Saeed's security fearing covert operation after J&K attack

description: Donald Trump asserted that Vladimir Putin wouldn't have invaded Ukraine if he were still president, suggesting Putin saw the Afghanistan withdrawal as a sign of weakness. Trump believes Putin initially aimed to seize all of Ukraine but his presence deterred him. He also stated that Putin now desires peace, possibly influenced by Trump's previous stance.
title: 'Putin would have gotten all of Ukraine if I hadn't won,' Trump claims
US secy speaks with Jaishankar, Pakistan PM; urges de-escalation of tensions
US, Ukraine sign minerals deal after two-month delay
